US President Donald Trump on Thursday defended saying he saw nothing wrong with receiving dirt on a political rival from a foreign government, even as his own Republicans joined a fierce backlash against the comments made in an interview with ABC News.  Trump says he welcomes foreign dirt on opponents President Donald Trump said on Wednesday he would see nothing wrong in accepting damaging information on a U.S. political opponent if it were offered to his re-election campaign by a foreign government. Jonah Green is on the story.